arXiv:2510.26331v3 Announce Type: replace-cross Abstract: We investigate the following Robin eigenvalue problem  egin{equation*} \left\{  egin{array}{ll} -\Delta u=\mu u\,\, &	ext{in}\,\, B,\ \partial_	exttt{n} u+\alpha u=0 &	ext{on}\,\, \partial B \end{array} ight. \end{equation*} on the unit ball of $\mathbb{R}^N$. We obtain the complete spectral structure of this problem. In particular, for $\alpha>0$, the first eigenvalue is $k_{
u,1}^2$ and the second eigenvalue is $k_{
u+1,1}^2$, where $k_{
u+l,m}$ is the $m$th positive zero of $kJ_{
u+l+1}(k)-(\alpha+l) J_{
u+l}(k)$. Moreover, when $\alpha\in(-l,1-l)$ with any $l\in \mathbb{N}$, one has $l$ negative (strictly increasing) eigenvalues $-\widehat{k}_{
u+i,1}^2$ with $i\in\{0,\ldots,l-1\}$ where $\widehat{k}_{
u+l,1}$ denotes the unique zero of $\alpha I_{
u+l}(k)+lI_{
u+l}(k)+kI_{
u+l+1}(k)$; while, for $\alpha=-l$, besides $l$ negative (increasing) eigenvalues, $0$ is also an eigenvalue.
